This paper analyzes the social sharing patterns of clickbait and non-clickbait tweets on Twitter, which involves studying the behavior of Twitter users and the content of tweets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of language in tweets, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The study of user engagement and organic reach of tweets can be categorized under cs.SOC (Social Computing). The paper also involves analyzing the content of tweets, which can be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of clickbait on news consumption, which can be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
